                "name": "Resolution",
                "url": "/topics/resolution"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682248",
        "quote": "I'm not one of those artists who doesn't want to play their most popular songs.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682248"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Most",
                "url": "/topics/most"
            },
            {
                "name": "Artists",
                "url": "/topics/artists"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682249",
        "quote": "Playing live was always definitely a lot more fun. You picture it: working alone in the studio eight or 10 hours a day with nobody else there, being frustrated and driven crazy by all of the things that you have to deal with, vs. thousands of people screaming and singing along with you playing.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682249"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deal",
                "url": "/topics/deal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Studio",
                "url": "/topics/studio"
            },
            {
                "name": "Frustrated",
                "url": "/topics/frustrated"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682250",
        "quote": "All Boston songs are fairly difficult to translate to the stage. None of them are especially easy to play or sing. A lot of them, of course, have very involved arrangements with lots of different sounds and sections that are difficult to play and sing. The prospect of doing any Boston song live is always an endeavor in itself.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682250"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Boston",
                "url": "/topics/boston"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682251",
        "quote": "There aren't a lot of cover bands that do Boston material or do it well, and the reason for that is that they are hard to play. So we put a lot of work into it. The musicians that I've managed to surround myself with after all of these years are individuals who really excel at what they do.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682251"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Boston",
                "url": "/topics/boston"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reason",
                "url": "/topics/reason"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682252",
        "quote": "When I first started recording, I was told by all of the experts in the business that the kind of music that I was doing was never going to sell. That disco was the coming thing and it was going to take over and what I was interested in was a minor sideline.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682252"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Business",
                "url": "/topics/business"
            },
            {
                "name": "Doing",
                "url": "/topics/doing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682253",
        "quote": "When I write a song and come up with an arrangement and a vocal part, it's always a challenge trying to find a singer who can interpret it sort of the way that I hear it, and it's a very difficult thing to do. I mean, singing is like playing an instrument - everybody does it a little bit different - singing maybe even more so.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682253"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Singer",
                "url": "/topics/singer"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everybody",
                "url": "/topics/everybody"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682254",
        "quote": "I don't plan tours necessarily around records. I know that's what most people do.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682254"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Know",
                "url": "/topics/know"
            },
            {
                "name": "Most",
                "url": "/topics/most"
            },
            {
                "name": "Records",
                "url": "/topics/records"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682255",
        "quote": "The studio work is the nasty, tedious, hard and nerve-wracking part, interrupted by moments of exhilaration. Playing live is the chance to actually have some fun and get on a stage.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682255"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Chance",
                "url": "/topics/chance"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Studio",
                "url": "/topics/studio"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682256",
        "quote": "I didn't touch a guitar until I was 20.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tom Scholz",
            "url": "/quotes/tom_scholz_682256"
        },
